tags.name: xtal-insert-json
tags.description: Combine passed-in JSON with JSON defined within script tag
tags.jsDoc:
/**
 * Combine passed-in JSON with JSON defined within script tag
 * @element xtal-insert-json
 *
 */

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description:
Any component that emits events should not do so if it is disabled.
Note that this is not enforced, but the disabled property is made available.
Users of this mix-in should ensure not to call "de" if this property is set to true.
attributes.jsDoc:
/**
         * Any component that emits events should not do so if it is disabled.
         * Note that this is not enforced, but the disabled property is made available.
         * Users of this mix-in should ensure not to call "de" if this property is set to true.
         * @attr
         */

attributes.name: with-path
input
attributes.description: An object that should be merged with the JSON inside the element

properties.name: evCount
properties.description: Tracks how many times each event type was called.

properties.name: withPath
input
properties.description: An object that should be merged with the JSON inside the element

properties.name: refs
properties.description: A key value pair object that allows the JSON to be passed functions or objects during the JSON parsing phase.

properties.name: mergedProp
postMergeCallbackFn
properties.description: Pass in a function to handle the resulting merged object, rather than using events.

properties.name: delay
properties.description: Number of milliseconds to wait before passing the input on for processing.

properties.name: objectsToMerge
properties.description: The object array that is to be merged.
